
CREATE TABLE

CREATE TABLE `user` (
  `id` INT NOT NULL,
  `name` VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
  `email` VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
  `gender` VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
  `status` VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
  PRIMARY KEY (`id`)
) ENGINE=INNODB DEFAULT CHARSET=utf8mb4 COLLATE=utf8mb4_0900_ai_ci



CREATE TABLE

CREATE TABLE `post` (
  `id` INT NOT NULL,
  `user_id` INT DEFAULT NULL,
  `title` VARCHAR(200) DEFAULT NULL,
  `body` TEXT,
  PRIMARY KEY (`id`),
  KEY `user_id` (`user_id`),
  CONSTRAINT `post_ibfk_1` FOREIGN KEY (`user_id`) REFERENCES `user` (`id`)
) ENGINE=INNODB DEFAULT CHARSET=utf8mb4 COLLATE=utf8mb4_0900_ai_ci

CREATE TABLE `comment` (
  `id` INT NOT NULL,
  `post_id` INT DEFAULT NULL,
  `name` VARCHAR(100) DEFAULT NULL,
  `email` VARCHAR(100) DEFAULT NULL,
  `body` TEXT,
  PRIMARY KEY (`id`),
  KEY `post_id` (`post_id`),
  CONSTRAINT `comment_ibfk_1` FOREIGN KEY (`post_id`) REFERENCES `post` (`id`)
) ENGINE=INNODB DEFAULT CHARSET=utf8mb4 COLLATE=utf8mb4_0900_ai_ci


Note : 

In project application.properties file ,
 provide your user name and password for DB and Authorization also.
 Also, mention your DB name and create the above tables and insert the data

URL : 

http://localhost:8080/test/posts

http://localhost:8080/test/users 

http://localhost:8080/test/comments


Import the project in eclipse after creating DF tables and populating the data.

Change the authorization details for the data base in the application.properties file 

once the project is ready , run the application and access the above end points from the browser or postman
